<bibRefCitation author="McPherson, J. E. &amp; Sites, R. W." box="[584,876,1195,1221]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="95 - 98" refId="ref55740" refString="McPherson, J. E. &amp; Sites, R. W. (1989) Annotated records of species of Pentatomoidea (Hemiptera) collected at light. The Great Lakes Entomologist, 22 (2), 95 - 98." type="journal article" year="1989">McPherson &amp; Sites 1989</bibRefCitation>
), FL, GA, LA (
<bibRefCitation author="Rosewall, O. W." box="[1055,1229,1195,1221]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="176 - 180" refId="ref60624" refString="Rosewall, O. W. (1922) Insects of the yellow thistle (Hem., Col., Lepid., Dip., Hym.). Entomological News, 33, 176 - 180." type="journal article" year="1922">Rosewall 1922</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="McPherson, R. M. &amp; Pitts, J. R. &amp; Newsom, L. D. &amp; Chapin, J. B. &amp; Herzog, D. C." pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="783 - 786" refId="ref56022" refString="McPherson, R. M., Pitts, J. R., Newsom, L. D., Chapin, J. B. &amp; Herzog, D. C. (1982) Incidence of tachinid parasitism of several stink bug (Heteroptera: Pentatomidae) species associated with soybean. Journal of Economic Entomology, 75 (5), 783 - 786. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / jee / 75.5.783" type="journal article" year="1982">
McPherson 
<emphasis box="[1378,1437,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">et al.</emphasis>
1982
</bibRefCitation>
), MS, TX. (
<collectingCountry box="[344,434,1231,1257]" name="Mexico" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, West Indies)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1159,1473]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,1266,1292]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Comments:</emphasis>
Many early workers misidentified this species, listing it under the name 
<taxonomicName authority="(Palisot de Beauvois)" baseAuthorityName="Palisot de Beauvois" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Euschistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifibulus">
<emphasis box="[1144,1368,1267,1293]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Euschistus bifibulus</emphasis>
(Palisot de Beauvois)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Barber, H. G." box="[357,517,1303,1329]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="241 - 244" refId="ref44713" refString="Barber, H. G. (1927) Two new species of Pentatomidae from the southern United States (Hemiptera-Heteroptera). Bulletin of the Brooklyn Entomological Society, 22 (5), 241 - 244." type="journal article" year="1927">Barber (1927)</bibRefCitation>
recognized that the species in the southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1021,1173,1303,1329]" name="United States of America" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">United States</collectingCountry>
was different from the true 
<taxonomicName box="[201,424,1339,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Euschistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifibulus">
<emphasis box="[201,424,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Euschistus bifibulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the West Indies. He described a new species, 
<taxonomicName box="[990,1279,1339,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Euschistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atromaculosus">
<emphasis box="[990,1279,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Euschistus atromaculosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, for the North American species. 
<bibRefCitation author="Barber, H. G. &amp; Bruner, S. C." box="[365,639,1375,1401]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="231 - 284" refId="ref44887" refString="Barber, H. G. &amp; Bruner, S. C. (1932) The Cydnidae and Pentatomidae of Cuba. Journal of the Department of Agriculture, Puerto Rico, 16 (3), 231 - 284, pls. 24 - 26. https: // doi. org / 10.46429 / jaupr. v 16 i 3.15048" type="journal article" year="1932">Barber &amp; Bruner (1932)</bibRefCitation>
placed 
<taxonomicName box="[728,1019,1375,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Euschistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atromaculosus">
<emphasis box="[728,1019,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Euschistus atromaculosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of this species. So, all early records of 
<taxonomicName box="[336,561,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Euschistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifibulus">
<emphasis box="[336,561,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Euschistus bifibulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the southern 
<collectingCountry box="[777,928,1411,1437]" name="United States of America" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">United States</collectingCountry>
should be transferred to this species. For example, the record listed above from 
<collectingRegion box="[556,666,1447,1473]" country="United States of America" name="Louisiana" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Louisiana</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rosewall, O. W." box="[681,851,1447,1473]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="176 - 180" refId="ref60624" refString="Rosewall, O. W. (1922) Insects of the yellow thistle (Hem., Col., Lepid., Dip., Hym.). Entomological News, 33, 176 - 180." type="journal article" year="1922">Rosewall 1922</bibRefCitation>
) is under the name 
<taxonomicName box="[1072,1297,1447,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Euschistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifibulus">
<emphasis box="[1072,1297,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Euschistus bifibulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
